"It is a truth universally acknowledged that compliance does not equal security. And yet too many organisations continue to exist in a state of cognitive dissonance in which they will readily agree that their compliance activities don't make them safe against today's threats while subconsciously thinking that they do. In this interview, Charles White, CEO of Information Risk Management (IRM), says it's time for organisations to bite the bullet and engage properly with information security. We all know that compliance does not equal security. And yet too many organisations continue to confuse the two issues. Part of the problem, argues Charles White, CEO of Information Risk Management (IRM), is that there has been so much pressure on organisations to become compliant that once they have achieved that painful goal they think the job is done. He says it's time for organisations to bite the bullet and engage properly with information security."
